.TH SRESET 2CCC
.SH NAME
sreset \- reset semaphore count
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B int sreset(sem,count)
.B int sem;
.B int count;
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Sreset
frees tasks in the queue for semaphore
.I sem,
and resets its count to
.I count.
This corresponds to the operations of sdelete(sem) and
sem=screate(count), except that it guarantees that the
semaphore id
.I sem
does not change.
The current count in a semaphore does not affect
resetting it.
.SH RETURN VALUE
If successful,
.I sreset
returns 0.  Otherwise, it returns -1 and errno is set to indicate the error.
.SH ERRORS
.TP 15
[EINVAL]
Invalid argument (
.I count
).
.TP 15
[CEBADSEM]
Invalid semaphore id.
.SH SEE ALSO
scount(2CCC), screate(2CCC), sdelete(2CCC), ssignal(2CCC), swait(2CCC)
